📊 Crime Data Analysis & Interactive Dashboard
🔷 Overview

This project analyzes real-world crime data to uncover patterns, trends, and insights using data analytics and visualization techniques. The dataset is sourced from the Los Angeles Police Department (LAPD) and covers crime incidents from 2020 to 2024.

The project focuses on transforming raw data into meaningful insights through an interactive dashboard built using Microsoft Power BI.

🎯 Objectives
Perform Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA)
Build an ETL pipeline (data cleaning & transformation)
Create an interactive dashboard
Identify trends based on time, location, and demographics
🛠️ Tools Used
Python (Pandas, NumPy)
Microsoft Power BI
Power Query
DAX
📊 Key Analysis
Crime by Hour & Day
Top Crime Areas
Crime Type Distribution
Case Status Analysis
Victim Age & Gender Analysis
🔍 Key Insights
Peak crime time: 5 PM – 8 PM
Lowest crime time: 4 AM – 5 AM
Most common crime: Vehicle Theft
Top 5 areas contribute ~30% of total crimes
Majority of cases remain under investigation
📈 Features
Interactive filters (slicers)
Dynamic charts & KPIs
Clean and intuitive dashboard design
🚀 Conclusion

This project demonstrates how data visualization and analytics can support data-driven decision-making in crime analysis and public safet
